%spark.pyspark
#We can also compute the correlation matrix and show the heatmap for it
from pyspark.mllib.stat import Statistics
import pandas as pd

col_names = datahour.columns[2:]
features = datahour.rdd.map(lambda row: row[2:])
corr_mat=Statistics.corr(features, method="pearson")
corr_df = pd.DataFrame(corr_mat)
corr_df.index, corr_df.columns = col_names, col_names

print(corr_df.to_string())

%spark.pyspark
import seaborn as sns

ax = sns.heatmap(
    corr_df, 
    vmin=-1, vmax=1, center=0,
    cmap=sns.diverging_palette(20, 220, n=200)
)
ax.set_xticklabels(
    ax.get_xticklabels(),
    rotation=45,
    horizontalalignment='right'
);

%md
Split the data into training and test data, with 70:30 split

msg.data: Split the data into training and test data, with 70:30 split

paragraphs.text:
%spark.pyspark
(training, test) = datahour.randomSplit([.7, .3])

%md

Use only numeric variables

%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import StringIndexer, OneHotEncoder, VectorAssembler, VectorIndexer
from pyspark.ml import Pipeline
from pyspark.sql.functions import *

#features
features = ['temp', 'hum', 'windspeed']
label = 'cnt'

training1 = training.select(col(label).alias("label"), *features)
print("Schema : ")
training1.printSchema()
print("First 5 rows : ")
training1.show(5)

test1 = test.select(col(label).alias("label"), *features)
print("First 5 rows : ")
test1.show(5)

%spark.pyspark

#transform the data 

vectorAssembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=features, outputCol="features")
training_transformed = vectorAssembler.transform(training1)
training_transformed.show(5, False)
%md

%spark.pyspark
#fit model with transformed training data 
lr = LinearRegression()
model1 = lr.fit(training_transformed)

%spark.pyspark
#model summary
summary = model1.summary
print("Model Summary :  ")
print("==========================================")
print ("##","Mean squared error: % .6f" \
  % summary.meanSquaredError, ", RMSE: % .6f" \
  % summary.rootMeanSquaredError )
print ("##","Multiple R-squared: %f" % summary.r2, ", \
  Total iterations: %i"% summary.totalIterations)

%spark.pyspark

test_transformed = vectorAssembler.transform(test1)
test_transformed.show(5, False)

#prediction
predictions = model1.transform(test_transformed)

# Select example rows to display.
print("\nModel Prediction Result :  ")
predictions.select("features","label","prediction").show(5)

%spark.pyspark
# Show model performance on test data using RegressionEvaluator 

evaluator1 = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label",
                                predictionCol="prediction",
                                metricName="rmse")
rmse1 = evaluator1.evaluate(predictions)
print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse1)


evaluator2 = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol="label",
                                predictionCol="prediction",
                                metricName="r2")
r21 = evaluator2.evaluate(predictions)
print("R-Squared on test data = %g" % r21)

paragraphs.text:
%md
Handling categorical features

%spark.pyspark
catcols = ['hr']
numcols = ['temp', 'hum', 'windspeed']
labelcol = 'cnt'

%spark.pyspark
indexer = StringIndexer(inputCol='hr', outputCol="{0}_indexed".format('hr'))

# default setting: dropLast=True
encoder = OneHotEncoder(inputCol=indexer.getOutputCol(),
            outputCol="{0}_encoded".format(indexer.getOutputCol()))

print("Indexed data:")
indexer = indexer.fit(training)
training_indexed = indexer.transform(training)
training_indexed.show(5)

print("Encoded data:")
training_encoded = encoder.transform(training_indexed)
training_encoded.show(5, False)

%spark.pyspark
assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=[encoder.getOutputCol()]
                                + numcols, outputCol="features")
training2 = assembler.transform(training_encoded)
training2 = training2.withColumn('label',col(labelcol)).select('features','label')
training2.show(5, False)

%spark.pyspark
print("Indexed data:")
test_indexed = indexer.transform(test)
test_indexed.show(5)

print("Encoded data:")
test_encoded = encoder.transform(test_indexed)
test_encoded.show(5, False)

test2 = assembler.transform(test_encoded)
test2 = test2.withColumn('label',col(labelcol)).select('features','label')
test2.show(5, False)

%spark.pyspark
featureIndexer = VectorIndexer(inputCol="features", \
                               outputCol="indexedFeatures",\
                               maxCategories=7).fit(training2)
lr = LinearRegression()

stages = [featureIndexer, lr]
pipeline2 = Pipeline(stages=stages)

model2 = pipeline2.fit(training2)

%spark.pyspark
#model summary
summary = model2.stages[-1].summary
print("Model Summary :  ")
print("==========================================")
print ("##","Mean squared error: % .6f" \
  % summary.meanSquaredError, ", RMSE: % .6f" \
  % summary.rootMeanSquaredError )
print ("##","Multiple R-squared: %f" % summary.r2, ", \
  Total iterations: %i"% summary.totalIterations)

%spark.pyspark
#prediction
predictions2 = model2.transform(test2)

# Select example rows to display.
print("\nModel Prediction Result :  ")
predictions2.select("features","label","prediction").show(5)

rmse2 = evaluator1.evaluate(predictions2)
print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse2)

r22 = evaluator2.evaluate(predictions2)
print("R-Squared on test data = %g" % r22)

%md
Save and Load Model

%spark.pyspark
filename='savedmodel.pkl'
model2.save(filename)

%spark.pyspark
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import PipelineModel

model3 = PipelineModel.load(filename)

#prediction
predictions3 = model3.transform(test2)

# Select example rows to display.
print("\nModel Prediction Result :  ")
predictions3.select("features","label","prediction").show(5)

rmse3 = evaluator1.evaluate(predictions3)
print("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) on test data = %g" % rmse3)

r23 = evaluator2.evaluate(predictions3)
print("R-Squared on test data = %g" % r23)
